The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar recorded a massive victory at the polling unit of Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue state. The PDP scored 286 votes leaving APC with zero vote at Tse Kondom Polling Unit, Nzorov Council Ward, where Gov Ortom voted. At the Senate level, the PDP’s Oker Jev had 289 while APC’s George Akume had no single vote. Ortom to Akume: Leave me alone, showcase your score card What Atiku’s candidature means for APC — Ojo Ogun APC gov candidate loses Polling unit to Atiku as Daniel wins for PDP